{"id":"309738262_A_small_deviation_inequality_for_convex_functions","abstract":"Let $Z$ be an $n$-dimensional Gaussian vector and let $f: \\mathbb R^n \\to \\mathbb R$ be a convex function. We show that: $$\\mathbb P \\left( f(Z) \\leq \\mathbb E f(Z) -t\\sqrt{ {\\rm Var} f(Z)} \\right) \\leq \\exp(-ct^2),$$ for all $t>1$, where $c>0$ is an absolute constant. As an application we derive refinements of the Johnson-Lindenstrauss flattening lemma and the random version of Dvoretzky's theorem.","authors":["Grigorios Paouris","Petros Valettas"],"meta":["November 2016The Annals of Probability 46(3)","DOI:10.1214/17-AOP1206"],"references":["301840852_Extensions_of_Lipschitz_mappings_into_a_Hilbert_space","38332459_Global_versus_local_asymptotic_theories_of_finite-dimensional_normed_spaces","2804364_Global_Vs_Local_Asymptotic_Theories_Of_Finite_Dimensional_Normed_Spaces","1741599_The_Johnson-Lindenstrauss_Lemma_Almost_Characterizes_Hilbert_Space_But_Not_Quite","315710622_Variance_estimates_and_almost_Euclidean_structure","299207427_The_random_version_of_dvoretzky's_theorem_in_linfinityn","285809848_A_new_proof_of_the_theorem_of_A_Dvoretzky_on_sections_of_convex_bodies","283279941_On_Dvoretzky's_theorem_for_subspaces_of_L_p","283279908_Random_version_of_Dvoretzky's_theorem_in_ell_pn","265549770_The_Random_Projection_Method","265372138_Asymptotic_theory_of_finite_dimensional_normed_spaces_With_an_appendix_by_M_Gromov_Isoperimetric_inequalities_in_Riemannian_manifolds","265332009_Symetrisation_dans_l'espace_de_Gauss","253127432_Uniform_almost_sub-Gaussian_estimates_for_linear_functionals_on_convex_sets","245665039_Classical_and_Modern_Fourier_Analysis","243769318_The_Concentration_of_Measure_Phenomenon","242103534_A_geometric_inequality_and_a_low_M-estimate","240326965_The_random_version_of_Dvoretzky's_theorem_in_'n1","227030158_Some_inequalities_for_Gaussian_processes_and_applications","225662278_Small_ball_probability_and_Dvoretzky's_Theorem","222429156_The_B_conjecture_for_